'''Jérémy Baffour Doku''' (born 27 May 2002) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]]. He is most known for his speed and dribbling ability.<ref>{{cite news |last=Clarke |first=Adrian |date=24 April 2025 |title=Analysis: Is Doku the best dribbler in the world? |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4293725 |access-date=10 November 2025 |publisher=Premier League}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=7 June 2023 |title=Jeremy Doku – Renaissance Man |website=Breaking The Lines |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/jeremy-doku-renaissance-man/ |access-date=10 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Balabanova |first=Lorihanna |date=1 November 2023 |title=Jérémy Doku Scout Report At Man City 2023/2024 – Analysis |website=Total Football Analysis |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/jeremy-doku-at-manchester-city-2023-24-scout-report-tactical-analysis |access-date=10 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Furniss |first=Matt |date=12 November 2023 |title=Jérémy Doku: So Good at Dribbling That Pep Guardiola Has Changed |url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/jeremy-doku-changed-pep-guardiola |access-date=10 November 2025 |website=Opta Analyst}}</ref>

Doku first gained prominence at [[RSC Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] as a 17-year-old before spending three years at [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]]. Manchester City signed him in August 2023 for €65 million; he won the [[2023–24 Premier League|Premier League title]] in his debut season.

Since 2020, Doku has been a regular Belgian international, having represented the nation in every [[Belgium national youth football team|youth level]] since the under-15s, and played at [[UEFA Euro 2020]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===Anderlecht===
[[File:Jérémy Doku.png|left|thumb|Doku with [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2019|301x301px]]
Doku began playing football at a young age in [[Antwerp]] for KVC Olympic Deurne and [[K. Tubantia Borgerhout V.K.|Tubantia Borgerhout]]; then he played for [[Germinal Beerschot|Beerschot]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Dimitri Charles |url=https://www.voetbalbelgie.be/specials/hoe-made-in-anderlecht-is-jeremy-doku/2020/09/09/ |title=HOE 'MADE IN ANDERLECHT' IS JÉRÉMY DOKU? |website=voetbalbelgie.be |language=nl |date=9 September 2020 }}</ref> Later on, he moved to [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2012 at the age of 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.anderlecht-online.be/fr/article/167935|title=Anderlecht Online – Doku a probablement le plus gros potentiel de Neerpede (présentation) (04 mai 18)|website=anderlecht-online.be}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Anderlecht in a 4–2 [[Belgian First Division A]] loss to [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] on 25 November 2018, at the age of 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/11/25/belgium/pro-league/sint-truidense-vv/royal-sporting-club-anderlecht/2794882/|title=Sint-Truiden vs. Anderlecht – 25 November 2018|website=Soccerway}}</ref> He was the seventh-youngest player to make his professional debut for Anderlecht, aged 16 years, 5 months and 26 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hln.be/de-krant/punten-verloren-zieltjes-gewonnen~af99bd46/ |title=Punten verloren, zieltjes gewonnen (Points lost, souls won)|website=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]] |language=nl |date=26 November 2018}}</ref>

On 1 December 2019, he scored his first professional goal in the league match against [[K.V. Oostende|KV Oostende]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/players/jeremy-doku|title=Jeremy Doku|website=mancity.com|access-date=25 May 2026}}</ref>

===Rennes===
====2020–2022: Debut season and injury problems====
On 5 October 2020, Doku signed for [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] for five years, for €26&nbsp;million in addition to bonuses, becoming the most expensive signing in the history of the club.<ref>{{cite web |date=25 October 2020 |title=Official: Jérémy Doku signs for Rennes for €26m + bonuses |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2020/official-jeremy-doku-signs-for-rennes-for-e26m-bonuses/ |website=Get French Football News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=25 October 2020 |title=JÉRÉMY DOKU EST ROUGE ET NOIR ! |url=https://www.staderennais.com/jeremy-doku-est-rouge-et-noir |website=Stade Rennais |language=fr}}</ref> The youngster struggled to make an impact in the first months at the new club, but started to pick up his form in December, contributing two assists against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] and [[FC Lorient|Lorient]].<ref name="footballghana.com">{{Cite web |date=11 January 2021 |title=Give youngster Jeremy Doku time to settle |url=https://footballghana.com/give-youngster-jeremy-doku-time-to-settle |website=Football Ghana}}</ref> Doku scored his first goal for Rennes on 20 March 2021, against [[FC Metz|Metz]], but was sent off for a bad challenge later in the same match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 March 2021 |title=Jeremy Doku scores but is sent off as Rennes beat John Boye's Metz |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/jeremy-doku-scores-but-is-sent-off-as-rennes-beat-john-boyes-metz |website=GhanaSoccernet}}</ref>

In his second season at Rennes, Doku scored one goal in [[Ligue 1]], having been limited to only 14 appearances by various injuries.<ref>{{Cite web |title=The many injuries are giving Jeremy Doku a tough time; it's mentally difficult for him – Stade Rennais manager reveals |url=https://footballghana.com/the-many-injuries-are-giving-jeremy-doku-a-tough-time-its-mentally-difficult-for-him-stade-rennais-manager-reveals |website=Football Ghana|date=12 October 2022 }}</ref> He started four matches and managed a total of 469 minutes over the course of the league campaign. On 2 January 2022, Doku scored the opening goal against [[AS Nancy Lorraine|Nancy]] in the fourth round of the [[2021–22 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]]; however, Rennes lost the match 5–4 on penalties, after the 120 minutes ended with the score 1–1.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Nancy – Rennes, le résumé du match |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/coupe-de-france/2021-2022/nancy-rennes-live/528684 |website=L'Equipe}}</ref>

====2022–2023: Return to form and departure====
In the first part of the [[2022–23 Ligue 1|2022–23 season]], Doku was mostly brought on as a substitute by Rennes manager [[Bruno Génésio]], but he returned to being a starter in the final months of the season. Following the departure of [[Kamaldeen Sulemana]] in the winter transfer window, Doku was handed the number 10 shirt, having previously worn number 11.<ref name=mancity2023>{{cite web|url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/jeremy-doku-signs-for-manchester-city-63828491|title=City complete signing of Jeremy Doku|first=Neil|last=Leigh|date=24 August 2023|access-date=25 May 2026|website=mancity.com}}</ref>

On 12 February 2023, in a 3–1 defeat against [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]], Doku played the full 90 minutes for the first time since 9 May 2021.<ref name=mancity2023/> Doku had an assist in each of the two legs of [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]]'s knockout round play-off against [[FC Shakhtar Donetsk|Shakhtar Donetsk]], but was unable to prevent his team from being eliminated from the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jeremy Doku provides assist in Stade Rennais defeat to Shakhtar Donetsk |url=https://footballghana.com/jeremy-doku-provides-assist-in-stade-rennais-defeat-to-shakhtar-donetsk |website=Football Ghana|date=24 February 2023 }}</ref> On 15 April, Doku scored his first brace for Rennes in a 3–0 home victory over [[Stade de Reims|Reims]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=One to Watch: Jérémy Doku |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Ligue-1-Show/2023/05/11/one-to-watch-jeremy-doku |website=Ligue 1}}</ref> The two goals against Reims were the first for Doku on Rennes' home ground [[Roazhon Park]] since he arrived at the club.

On 30 April, Doku had another brace against [[Angers SCO|Angers]], securing his team a 4–2 win after scoring the final two goals in the second half.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ligue 1 roundup: Doku stars as Rennes score four while Nice and Clermont snatch wins |url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/soccer-ligue-1-ligue-1-roundup-doku-stars-as-rennes-score-four-while-nice-and-clermont-snatch-wins/zoW2Nfhm/ |website=Flashscore}}</ref> On 21 May, he scored the third goal in Rennes' 5–0 win away against [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]], a solo effort for which he started his run with the ball towards the opposition's goal from inside his team's half. Doku finished the season with six goals in the league, helping Rennes to a fourth-place finish.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4702691/2023/07/27/jeremy-doku-rennes-dribbling-machine/|title=Jeremy Doku: Rennes’ electrifying two-footed dribbling machine|first=Ahmed|last=Walid|date=26 July 2023|access-date=25 May 2026|newspaper=The New York Times}}</ref>

[[File:Lens - Stade Rennais (20-08-2023) 55.jpg|thumb|260px|Doku warming up for his last game for Rennes, a few days before his transfer to Manchester City was officialised]]

On 13 August, Doku scored a goal in Rennes' 5–1 win against [[FC Metz|Metz]] in their first match of the [[2023–24 Ligue 1]] season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Rennes – Metz : le SRFC débute par un festival offensif |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2023-2024/rennes-metz-live/594748 |access-date=13 August 2023 |website=L'Equipe}}</ref> He played his final match for Rennes on 20 August, as a substitute in a 1–1 draw against [[RC Lens|Lens]]. The next day, it was reported that Rennes accepted a £55&nbsp;million (€65&nbsp;million) offer from English club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for the transfer of Doku to the [[Premier League]] champions.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Thomas |first=Lyall |title=Jeremy Doku: Man City agree £55.5m deal to sign Belgian winger from French club Rennes |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11679/12944715/jeremy-doku-manchester-city-agree-55-5m-deal-to-sign-belgian-winger-from-french-club-rennes |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Oldham |first=Lewis |title=Man City set to sign €65m ex-Liverpool target as 'agreement' is reached after 'new bid' |url=https://www.football365.com/news/man-city-set-sign-e65m-ex-liverpool-target-agreement-reached-new-bid |access-date=23 August 2023 |website=Football365|date=21 August 2023 }}</ref> According to ''[[The Guardian]]'', both club and player rejected an official bid from [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] before finalising the agreement with City.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Steinberg |first=Jacob |date=21 August 2023 |title=West Ham bid for Jérémy Doku but struggle to agree Mohammed Kudus fee |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/20/west-ham-bid-for-jeremy-doku-but-struggle-to-agree-mohammed-kudus-fee |website=The Guardian}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
====2023–2024: Adaptation and first league title====
On 24 August 2023, City confirmed the signing of Doku on a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=City complete signing of Jeremy Doku |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/jeremy-doku-signs-for-manchester-city-63828491 |date=24 August 2023 |access-date=24 August 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> He was presented with the number 11 shirt for the [[2023–24 Premier League|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Doku's squad number revealed |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/jeremy-doku-man-city-shirt-number-63828492 |date=24 August 2023 |access-date=24 August 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> On 2 September, he made his debut for City in a 5–1 win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] at the [[City of Manchester Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bray |first=Joe |title=Why Jeremy Doku was left 'frustrated' with Man City debut despite 5–1 win vs Fulham |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/doku-man-city-fulham-haaland-27641841 |access-date=4 September 2023 |website=Manchester Evening News|date=2 September 2023 }}</ref> On 16 September, he scored his first goal in a 3–1 away win over West Ham United.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/west-ham-united-v-city-match-report-63830469 |title=City fight back to win Hammers thriller and maintain perfect start |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=16 September 2023 }}</ref> After the match, City manager [[Pep Guardiola]] stated that he did not expect that kind of performance from Doku in his second appearance for the new club, calling him a "proper winger" and further adding "the way he played today, I don't remember something like that since a long time ago".<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Connor |first=Robert |date=16 September 2023 |title=Pep Guardiola hails impact of Jeremy Doku in Man City's win at West Ham |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/pep-guardiola-west-ham-premier-league-alphonse-areola-rennes-b2412901.html |website=The Independent}}</ref>

On 4 October, Doku scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in the group game against German team [[RB Leipzig]], rounding off a counterattack in stoppage time to convert [[Julián Álvarez]]'s pass, sealing City's 3–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=RB Leipzig 1–3 Man City: Alvarez, Doku secure City win with late goals from bench |url=https://www.football365.com/news/rb-leipzig-1-3-man-city-alvarez-doku-secure-city-win-late-goals-bench |access-date=5 October 2023 |website=Football365|date=4 October 2023 }}</ref> The goal followed a reversal of the roles between the two players, as only a few minutes earlier Álvarez scored City's second goal from Doku's assist.<ref>{{Cite web |title=RB Leipzig 1–3 Man City: Julian Alvarez and Jeremy Doku give Champions League holders deserved win in Germany |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/26806/12975562/rb-leipzig-1-3-man-city-julian-alvarez-and-jeremy-doku-give-champions-league-holders-deserved-win-in-germany |website=Sky Sports |date=5 October 2023 }}</ref> 
[[File:2023-10-04_Fußball,_Männer,_UEFA_Champions_League,_RB_Leipzig_-_Manchester_City_FC_IMG_6166.jpg|thumb|Doku scored his first Champions League goal against [[RB Leipzig]] in [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|October 2023]]]]
Doku had another assist to Álvarez on 22 October, in the Premier League match against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.–Crystal Palace F.C. rivalry|Brighton & Hove Albion]], which City won 2–1. He was named player of the match after repeatedly beating [[James Milner]] on the left side during the game; former City player [[Paul Dickov]] commented that he "felt sorry for Milner" after the match, and that Doku looked a threat "every time he had the ball".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=22 October 2023 |title=Impressive Doku has settled quickly, says Dickov |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/dickov-praises-doku-matchday-live-reaction-63833580 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref>

On 4 November, Doku scored the opening goal and added four assists in a 6–1 win over [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]], becoming the youngest player in Premier League history at 21 years and 161 days of age to provide four assists and have five direct goal involvements in a single match.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mills |first=Richard |date=4 November 2023 |title=Unstoppable! Jeremy Doku bags two Premier League records after grabbing four assists and one goal as Man City smash Bournemouth for six |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/jeremy-doku-two-premier-league-records-four-assists-one-goal-man-city-smash-bournemouth-six/bltf55e81fa93df5119 |website=Goal (website)}}</ref> With the four assists, Doku tied the Premier League record for most assists in a match and was given the player of the match award for his performance.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=4 November 2023 |title=DOKU DAZZLES AS SUPER CITY HIT SIX TO MOVE TOP OF THE PREMIER LEAGUE |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-bournemouth-match-report-november-4-63834704 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> On 3 December against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham]], Doku suffered a hamstring injury that kept him on the sidelines for a month.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Marrett |first=Adam |date=1 January 2024 |title=Jeremy Doku could be back for Manchester City within weeks |url=https://esteemedkompany.com/2024/01/01/jeremy-doku-could-be-back-for-manchester-city-within-weeks/ |website=Esteemed Kompany}}</ref> On 7 January 2024, he returned in the third round of the [[FA Cup]] against [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]], scoring the final goal in a 5–0 win for Manchester City, his first in English cup competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Doku |first=Cephas |date=7 January 2024 |title=Jeremy Doku stars as Manchester City crush Huddersfield Town in FA Cup |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/jeremy-doku-stars-as-manchester-city-crush-huddersfield-town-in-fa-cup |website=Ghana Soccernet}}</ref>

On 13 April, Doku was voted man of the match in the 5–1 win against [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]], after he scored a goal, made an assist to [[Joško Gvardiol]], and won a penalty which was converted by [[Erling Haaland]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=13 April 2024 |title=Manchester City's Jérémy Doku and Josko Gvardiol complete Luton rout |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/apr/13/manchester-city-luton-premier-league-match-report |access-date=13 April 2024 |work=The Observer |language=en-GB |issn=0029-7712}}</ref> On 17 April, Doku entered the Champions League quarter-final return leg against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] as a substitute and made the cross for Kevin De Bruyne's equalising goal in the second half, in addition to creating several other chances. After the match Pep Guardiola stated that Doku changed the game with his chance creation.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=22 April 2024 |title=Pep Guardiola says he actually told £55m Man City ace he used to be poor off the bench |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/pep-guardiola-says-he-actually-told-55m-man-city-player-doku-he-used-to-be-poor-off-the-bench/ |access-date=30 April 2024 |website=Manchester City News |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 20 April, in the FA Cup semi-final match against Chelsea, Doku had similar impact, as once again he came on in the second half and had a major contribution in [[Bernardo Silva]]'s winning goal. Former Manchester City winger [[Shaun Wright-Phillips]] had a similar comment after the match as the Manchester City manager few days earlier: "Doku coming on changed the game for us. He was fantastic, he just brings something different against the low block".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=21 April 2024 |title=Shaun Wright-Phillips says £55m star actually 'changed the game' for Man City vs Chelsea |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/shaun-wright-phillips-says-fantastic-55m-star-doku-actually-changed-the-game-for-man-city-vs-chelsea/ |access-date=30 April 2024 |website=Manchester City News |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 19 May, Doku assisted [[Phil Foden]]'s second goal in Manchester City's 3–1 win against West Ham in the final match of the season, which sealed the title in the Premier League, first in Doku's career.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=19 May 2024 |title=CITY MAKE HISTORY AS WIN OVER WEST HAM SECURES RECORD FOURTH TITLE |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-west-ham-premier-league-match-report-63851724 |website=mancity.com}}</ref> He was one of only three players aged under 21 who had eleven or more combined league goals and assists in the 2023–24 season, together with [[Rasmus Højlund]] and [[Alejandro Garnacho]]. On 25 May, Doku scored in the FA Cup final against Manchester United, but his team lost 2–1, thus failing to lift the double.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Man City 1–2 Man Utd: Erik ten Hag's side end season on high with stunning FA Cup final win at Wembley |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/man-city-vs-man-utd/report/504674 |access-date=28 May 2024 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref>

====2024–2025: Sporadic contributions during team decline====
On 24 September, Doku scored his first goal of the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]], opening the scoreline in a 2–1 win against [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in the third round of the [[Carabao Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=24 September 2024 |title=Academy aces help City to Carabao Cup win over Watford |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/city-v-watford-carabao-cup-match-report-63862803 |website=Mancity.com}}</ref> On 1 October, Doku had 26 touches in the box in the 4–0 win against [[ŠK Slovan Bratislava|Slovan Bratislava]] in the Champions League, breaking the previous record for number of touches in the opposition's box that stood since the 2008–09 season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=2 October 2024 |title=Jeremy Doku did something no other player has in the UCL since the 2008/2009 season against Slovan Bratislava |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/man-citys-jeremy-doku-did-something-no-other-player-has-in-the-champions-league-since-the-2008-2009-season/ |access-date=8 October 2024 |website=Manchester City News |language=en-GB}}</ref> He made one assist to Phil Foden in the match, which he followed up in the next Premier League match on 5 October against Fulham, with a goal scored from outside the box to secure a 3–2 win.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hunter |first=Laura |date=5 October 2024 |title=Man City 3–2 Fulham: Mateo Kovacic double and Jeremy Doku stunner ensure Pep Guardiola's side keep pressure on Liverpool |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/26806/13226586/man-city-3-2-fulham-mateo-kovacic-double-and-jeremy-doku-stunner-ensure-pep-guardiolas-side-keep-pressure-on-liverpool |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241005183217/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/26806/13226586/man-city-3-2-fulham-mateo-kovacic-double-and-jeremy-doku-stunner-ensure-pep-guardiolas-side-keep-pressure-on-liverpool |archive-date=5 October 2024 |access-date=22 June 2025 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 19 January 2025, Doku scored City's third goal and assisted Erling Haaland's fourth in the 6–0 win against [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]], eliciting praise from manager Pep Guardiola, who called his performance in the match "brilliant".<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 January 2025 |title='Today was different' Pep Guardiola gives Jeremy Doku verdict after Man City thrash Ipswich |url=https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/today-different-pep-guardiola-gives-060000463.html |access-date=20 January 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-GB}}</ref> However, in the same match he suffered an injury which sidelined him for almost a month.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 January 2025 |title=Pep Guardiola confirms Jeremy Doku injury blow as Man City winger ruled out 'for a while' {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/pep-guardiola-confirms-jeremy-doku-injury-blow-man-city-winger-ruled-out-for-a-while/blt01462a5826085208#cs8085ad58d41d0ca0 |access-date=26 February 2025 |website=Goal (website) |language=en}}</ref> Doku's absence has compounded an injury crisis at Manchester City, which together with ageing key players like De Bruyne, Bernardo Silva and [[İlkay Gündoğan]] has led to a sharp drop of form in Guardiola's squad, falling outside of the title race in the Premier League in the first half of the season and getting eliminated from the Champions League playoffs.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 February 2025 |title=From bad to worse? Man City facing battle just to qualify for Champions League |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/43993067/could-man-city-miss-champions-league-qualification |access-date=27 February 2025 |publisher=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=20 December 2024 |title=Guardiola's Man City Crisis: Causes, Solutions & Future Plans {{!}} Analysis |url=https://mancitysquare.com/guardiola-s-man-city-crisis-causes-solutions-future-plans |access-date=27 February 2025 |website=Man City Square |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=12 February 2025 |title=Manchester City's ageing squad brutally exposed by Real Madrid in Champions League defeat |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ce3l0ve5v1vo |access-date=27 February 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>
[[File:2023-10-04 Fußball, Männer, UEFA Champions League, RB Leipzig - Manchester City FC 1DX 2767 (Jérémy Doku).jpg|thumb|upright|Doku in 2023]]
On 23 February 2025 in a 2–0 loss against Liverpool, Doku set a season record for completed dribbles in the Premier League with 13 successful take-ons, most of them against England international [[Trent Alexander-Arnold]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Most Successful Dribbles In One Game |url=https://www.statmuse.com/fc/ask/most-successful-dribbles-in-one-game |access-date=26 February 2025 |website=StatMuse |language=en}}</ref> On 27 February, Doku won the man of the match award in the 1–0 win over Tottenham, after providing an assist for Haaland's lone goal, and creating most chances in the match out any player on the pitch.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fell |first=Tyler |date=26 February 2025 |title=Tottenham Hotspur 0–1 Manchester City: Player ratings and match highlights |url=https://www.givemesport.com/tottenham-hotspur-manchester-city-player-ratings-match-highlights-2025/ |access-date=27 February 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> On 22 April, he entered against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the second half and assisted [[Matheus Nunes]]' match winning goal against in extra time, helping his team make a major step in the push for a Champions League spot with the 2–1 win against a direct rival from the top of the table. Pep Guardiola stated after the match that Doku is the best player in the world in the first few meters, unstoppable in the final third, and "an incredible football player", noting that he has been unfair to Doku for not starting him in recent matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 April 2025 |title='I've been so unfair' – Pep Guardiola apologises to 'incredible' Jeremy Doku after dropping Man City winger to the bench {{!}} Goal.com English Oman |url=https://www.goal.com/en-om/lists/i-ve-been-so-unfair-pep-guardiola-apologises-incredible-jeremy-doku-after-dropping-man-city-winger-bench/bltef1d737062fb436d#cs5ed98ec5decc8960 |access-date=23 April 2025 |website=Goal (website) |language=en-OM}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Nzyoki |first=Gedion |date=23 April 2025 |title=Pep Guardiola Declares Manchester City Star 'Best in the World' in First Five Metres |url=https://www.msn.com/en-xl/africa/kenya/pep-guardiola-declares-manchester-city-star-best-in-the-world-in-first-five-metres/ar-AA1Drk8Z |publisher=MSN}}</ref>

Doku scored two goals during Manchester City's [[FIFA Club World Cup]] campaign in June 2025, against [[Wydad AC|Wydad]] and [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the group stage. City were eliminated from the tournament in the quarterfinals by [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Saudi club Al Hilal stun Man City 4–3 to enter Club World Cup quarters |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2025/7/1/al-hilal-stun-man-city-4-3-to-enter-club-world-cup-quarterfinals |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=Al Jazeera |language=en}}</ref> Doku finished the season with 8 goals and 11 assists in 46 matches across all competitions, while also leading the Premier League in several advanced analytics categories, like progressive carries, duels won, percentage of completed dribbles, and completed dribbles per 90 minutes, a category in which he led all of the players in Europe.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clarke |first=Adrian |date=24 April 2025 |title=Analysis: Is Doku the best dribbler in the world? |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4293725 |access-date=3 June 2025 |publisher=Premier League |language=en}}</ref>

==== 2025–2026: First team regular ====
After a slow start to the season in August, entering two out of the first three Premier League matches as a substitute, and being largely ineffective from the wing, Doku switched to a more central role in Pep Guardiola's tactics in September, with more freedom to roam towards the inside spaces.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 September 2025 |title=Jérémy Doku Could Be More Than Just A Killer Wiggle {{!}} Defector |url=https://defector.com/jeremy-doku-could-be-more-than-just-a-killer-wiggle |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=defector.com |language=en}}</ref> The tactical adjustment yielded immediate results, as Doku assisted Foden and Haaland in the 3–0 win against city rivals Manchester United.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Irfan |first=Umir |date=15 September 2025 |title=Man City 3–0 Man Utd: Where was the Manchester derby won and lost? |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ckge4jpy4l5o |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> His first assist was particularly impressive, as he received the ball in the middle and dribbled past [[Luke Shaw]] before crossing to Foden.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kompany |first=Esteemed |date=15 September 2025 |title=A Manchester City winger did everything he had to do against Manchester United |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/manchester-city-winger-did-everything-070500118.html |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> Doku joined Haaland and James Milner as only the third player ever to record multiple assists in a single Manchester derby match.

On 18 September, Doku scored his first goal of the season in the 2–0 Champions League win against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]], once again providing a spectacular highlight, as he picked up the ball right in front of the box and dribbled through several opposition players before slotting past [[Vanja Milinković-Savić|Milinković-Savić]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=18 September 2025 |title=Doku decorates Manchester City's win over Napoli after De Bruyne return ends early |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/sep/18/manchester-city-napoli-champions-league-match-report |access-date=9 November 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 27 September, Doku continued his excellent form, receiving the man of the match award against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], where he made an assist to Haaland and forced an own goal by [[Maxime Estève]] in a 5–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bate |first=Adam |date=27 September 2025 |title=Man City 5–1 Burnley: Maxime Esteve scores two own goals before Erling Haaland's brace takes City up to fourth |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13438093/man-city-3-1-burnley-maxime-esteve-scored-two-goals-as-pep-guardiola-s-side-climb-to-fifth-in-the-table |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> He also set the season's record for touches in the opposition's box with 21, becoming the only City player to have more than 20 touches in the opposition box in a Premier League match since Pep Guardiola took charge.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Palmer |first=Ben |date=30 September 2025 |title=Stats prove that 23-year-old star Pep Guardiola likened to Raheem Sterling can revive Man City's season |url=https://www.footballinsider247.com/stats-show-man-city-player-who-pep-guardiola-likened-to-raheem-sterling-can-transform-their-season/ |access-date=10 November 2025 |website=Football Insider |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 29 October, Doku scored his season's first goal in the English cup competitions in a 3–1 win away at [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in the [[EFL Cup]].

On 5 November, Doku was again one of City's best players in a 4–1 win against [[Borussia Dortmund]], providing an assist for Haaland, while also creating  most chances, completing most dribbles, being the most fouled player and winning the most duels in the match.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guyett |first=Matthew |date=5 November 2025 |title=Forget Haaland and Foden: Man City Gem Announced Himself as 'World-Class' vs Dortmund |url=https://www.givemesport.com/man-city-jeremy-doku-proved-world-class-borussia-dortmund/ |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref> Four days later, he scored the third goal in a 3–0 win at home against Liverpool and won the man of the match award again in his 100th appearance for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mumford |first=Jack |title=Doku's standout games at City so far |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/Doku%E2%80%99s%20standout%20games%20at%20City%20so%20far |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=Manchester City FC |language=en}}</ref> Against Liverpool, Doku became the first player with more than ten dribbles, more than ten duels won, more than both three chances created and three shots on target, and a goal scored in a Premier League match, since Eden Hazard in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Keble |first=Alex |date=9 November 2025 |title='Outstanding' Doku sends Liverpool back into a spin |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4460730/outstanding-doku-sends-liverpool-back-into-a-spin |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref> ''[[The Sporting News]]''<nowiki/>' Joe Wright called Doku's performance "his finest in the blue shirt", while commentator [[Gary Neville]] awarded him the Player of the Match award after only an hour played.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wright |first=Joe |date=9 November 2025 |title=Jeremy Doku stats today: Manchester City winger dazzles in Premier League clash with Liverpool |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/jeremy-doku-stats-today-manchester-183852053.html |access-date=9 November 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 26 April 2026, Doku came off the bench in the FA Cup semifinal match against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] to score the equalizer and assist [[Nico González (footballer, born 2002)|Nico González]] for the winner, helping City reach a record fourth succesive FA Cup final with a 2–1 win against the Saints at Wembley.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hampson |first=Andy |date=27 April 2026 |title=Jeremy Doku hails Man City's history-makers as he targets FA Cup glory |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/jeremy-doku-man-city-fa-cup-wembley-b2965448.html |access-date=4 May 2026 |website=The Independent |language=en}}</ref> On 4 May, he scored his first Premier League brace, as he opened the scoring against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], and then scored a curling shot from the edge of the box in the last minute of the match to earn his side a 3–3 draw, keeping City's title chances alive.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hunter |first=Andy |date=4 May 2026 |title=Manchester City's wild draw at Everton hands Arsenal title edge despite late Doku strike |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/may/04/everton-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report |access-date=4 May 2026 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 16 May, he won his first [[FA Cup]] as a Man City player, after losing the final in the previous two years.

==International career==
[[File:Jérémy Doku USMNT v Belgium Mar 28 2026-169 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Doku in 2026]]

=== 2017–2020: Youth level and senior team debut ===
Doku represented the [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium U17s]] at the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Nos −17 échouent en demi-finale – Union Royale Belge des Sociétés de Football-Association |url=http://www.belgianfootball.be/fr/nouvelles/s%C3%A9lection-uefa-european-under-17-championship-2018 |publisher=Royal Belgian Football Association}}</ref> as well as the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Belgium-Republic of Ireland &#124; UEFA Under-17 2019 |url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2027416--belgium-vs-republic-of-ireland/}}</ref> Doku made his first appearance for the Belgium national team on 5 September 2020 against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] in the [[UEFA Nations League]]. Three days later, he scored his first goal for the Belgium national team in a 5–1 win against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]].<ref>{{cite web |date=8 September 2020 |title=Belgium 5–1 Iceland: Red Devils top of group after rampant display |url=https://www.goal.com/en/match/belgium-v-iceland/report/6ziw11murei1tmjqbzxm1nxii |website=Goal (website)}}</ref>

=== 2021–2024: Early international career and first major tournaments ===
In the [[UEFA Euro 2020]], held in June 2021, Doku was one of the substitutes for the Belgium national team in their group stage match against Denmark, and was included in the starting line-up for the subsequent game against [[Finland national football team|Finland]]. He was again named to the starting eleven for Belgium's quarter-final 2–1 loss against [[Italy national football team|Italy]], where he won a penalty for his team and set the record for duels won in the tournament, as part of a performance that has since been considered his breakout moment in top level football.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Memon |first=Taha |date=2 July 2021 |title=Belgium starboy Jeremy Doku shines against Italy – here's what he once said of Liverpool's interest in him |url=https://tribuna.com/en/news/liverpoolfc-2021-07-02-belgium-starboy-jeremy-doku-shines-against-italy-heres-what-he-once-said-of-liverpools-in/ |access-date=3 July 2021 |website=Tribuna}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Curtis |first=Leigh |date=2 July 2021 |title=Jeremy Doku would 'explode' at Leicester City amid stunning transfer demand |url=https://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/jeremy-doku-leicester-city-transfer-5606128 |website=Leicestershire Live}}</ref> In November 2022, Doku was called up by manager [[Roberto Martínez]] to the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium squad]] that would compete for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] held in [[Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=December 2022 |title=FFT Belgium squad WC2022 |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/belgium-world-cup-2022-squad-players-line-up-qatar}}</ref> He made his World Cup debut as a substitute in Belgium's final group match against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Julien |first=Laurens |date=December 2022 |title=Croatia reach World Cup round of 16 as Belgium's golden generation stay trophy-less |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37634459/croatia-reach-world-cup-last-16-belgium-golden-generation-goes-home |publisher=ESPN}}</ref>

After [[Eden Hazard]]'s post-World Cup retirement from the Belgium national team, Doku was given a more prominent role in the squad by new manager [[Domenico Tedesco]]. On 12 September 2023, Doku recorded an assist in the 5–0 win over [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]] in the Group F qualifiers for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]], and was subsequently given the man of the match award.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Procter |first=Tom |date=13 September 2023 |title='Amazing' £55m Man City star sends message to Pep with dazzling MOTM display in 5–0 international win |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/amazing-55m-man-city-player-dazzles-for-his-country-in-5-0-win-sends-message-to-pep/ |website=Manchester City News}}</ref> In Belgium's next qualifying match on 13 October, against [[Austria national football team|Austria]], Doku helped the national team to a 3–2 win and the securing of qualification for the Euro 2024, as he provided another assist for [[Romelu Lukaku]]'s winning goal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 October 2023 |title=KIJK. De beste dribbelaar van Europa: dit waren alle 15 flitsen van Jérémy Doku tegen Oostenrijk |url=https://www.hln.be/rode-duivels/kijk-de-beste-dribbelaar-van-europa-dit-waren-alle-15-flitsen-van-jeremy-doku-tegen-oostenrijk~a30469ac/ |website=HLN}}</ref>

Doku was a starter in all of Belgium's UEFA Euro 2024 matches. His best performance came on 22 June 2025 in the group stage against [[Romania national football team|Romania]], where he once again set the tournament record for completed take-ons (9) in a single match.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=23 June 2024 |title=Stat shows Jeremy Doku has done something no other player has at Euro 2024 so far |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/stat-shows-jeremy-doku-did-something-against-romania-no-other-player-has-at-euro-2024-so-far/ |access-date=19 November 2025 |website=Manchester City News |language=en-GB}}</ref> Despite his team's elimination in the first knockout round by [[France national football team|France]], Doku completed 34 dribbles in the tournament, more than any other player.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=The official website for European football |url=https://www.uefa.com/errors/ |access-date=15 July 2024 |publisher=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref> The second best ranked [[Lamine Yamal]] had 32 dribbles while playing three more matches than Doku.

=== 2025–present: Key player in World Cup qualifiers ===
On 9 June 2025, Doku scored the third goal in the 4–3 win against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] in the World Cup 2026 qualifiers, his first goal for the national team since 30 March 2021 against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Belgium 4–3 Wales: World Cup qualifier – Late Kevin de Bruyne strike wins Brussels thriller |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c7539d4zw4dt |access-date=8 September 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 7 September, he scored his first brace in the Belgium shirt in the World Cup qualifying match against [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]], which the Belgians won 6–0 at home.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Belgium vs Kazakhstan: UEFA World Cup Qualifiers stats & head-to-head |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c14g41ve3k7t |access-date=8 September 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 19 November, Doku scored another brace and provided an assist to [[Charles De Ketelaere]], helping Belgium to a 7–0 victory over [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] to secure their spot at the 2026 World Cup.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Belgium 7–0 Liechtenstein: Doku and De Ketelaere star in thumping win |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-my/football/uefa-world-cup-qualifiers/articles/belgium-7-0-liechtenstein-doku-and-de-ketelaere-star-in-thumping-win-2025-11-18 |access-date=19 November 2025 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-asia}}</ref>

==Player profile==
===Style of play===
Doku is equally comfortable playing on the left wing and on the right wing. According to ''[[The Athletic]]'', Doku is "a ball-to-feet winger who constantly changes his positioning to present himself as a progressive passing option".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Walid |first=Ahmed |title=Jeremy Doku: Rennes' electrifying two-footed dribbling machine |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4702691/2023/07/27/jeremy-doku-rennes-dribbling-machine/ |access-date=30 July 2023 |website=The Athletic}}</ref> Doku is naturally right-footed, but he also has a strong left foot which he often uses to shoot at the goal after cutting in from the right side or cross from the left. An extremely quick and explosive player with great acceleration, agility, balance and body strength,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Wonderkids: Jérémy Doku |url=https://soccerment.com/wonderkids-jeremy-doku/ |website=Soccerment|date=12 January 2021 }}</ref> Doku is most known for his elite dribbling skills, flair and trickery.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Terreur |first=Kristof |date=2 June 2021 |title=Jérémy Doku: the Belgium prodigy who got away from Liverpool |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jun/02/jeremy-doku-the-belgium-prodigy-who-got-away-from-liverpool |access-date= |website=The Guardian}}</ref> His low centre of gravity, body control, unpredictable footwork and rapid change of pace has helped him become one of the world's most effective forward in one-on-one situations.<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 March 2021 |title=Statattack Round 29: Doku the dribble king! |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/News/2021/03/16/statattack-round-29-doku-the-dribble-king-mbappe-neymar |website=Ligue 1}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Bhavsar |first=Jimit |title=Top five players with most take-ons completed in 2022–23 season |url=https://khelnow.com/football/2023-06-world-football-players-most-take-ons-2022-23completed |website=KhelNow}}</ref> Doku's signature move is the shoulder drop, putting his right foot over the ball and making a feint towards the inside, forcing the defender to lean in, followed by a sudden burst to the right, as he keeps the ball under close control. He also frequently uses a drag-back spin move when backed against defenders, turning quickly and advancing up the pitch.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=31 March 2025 |title=Become a Pro: Mastering the Art of Playing Like Jeremy Doku |url=https://thetitansfa.com/become-a-pro-mastering-the-art-of-playing-like-jeremy-doku/ |access-date=23 November 2025 |website=Titans Football |language=en-GB}}</ref>

As a youth player, Doku was called "arrogant" for his tendency to wait for opposition defenders to recover so he could repeatedly beat them with the ball.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hendrix |first=Hale |title=Jeremy Doku Childhood Story Plus Untold Biography Facts |url=https://lifebogger.com/jeremy-doku-childhood-biography-story-facts/ |access-date=2 July 2023 |website=Life Bogger |archive-date=8 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230708090027/https://lifebogger.com/jeremy-doku-childhood-biography-story-facts/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Doku declared himself in 2021 "the best dribbler in Ligue 1".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Peter |first=McVitie |title=NXGN star Doku: I'm a better dribbler than Neymar or Mbappe |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/nxgn-star-doku-im-a-better-dribbler-than-neymar-or-mbappe/1rjht8kajxw8y1y1mbtb3puvnq |access-date=28 March 2021 |website=Goal (website)}}</ref> Due to his directness, he draws a lot of fouls from opponents, having received a foul once every 35 minutes on average, resulting with him being the tenth-most-fouled player in Ligue 1 in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |last=McAleer |first=Ben |date=22 August 2023 |title=Why Man City are prepared to spend big on wing-wizard Jeremy Doku |url=https://www.whoscored.com/Articles/0U7JaSCVwk605Wj_4SF2mg/Show/Why-Man-City-are-prepared-to-spend-big-on-wing-wizard-Jeremy-Doku |website=WhoScored.com}}</ref> Doku also possesses excellent vision and crossing ability, completing more than 80 per cent of his passes;<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jeremy Doku – Renaissance Man |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/jeremy-doku-renaissance-man/ |access-date=7 June 2023 |website=Breaking the Lines|date=7 June 2023 }}</ref> however, he has been criticised for his lack of end product,<ref name="ligue1.com">{{Cite web |title=One to watch: Jérémy Doku, Rennes' key to beating PSG? |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/ONE-TO-WATCH/2021/05/03/jeremy-doku-rennes-key-to-beating-psg |access-date=5 March 2021 |website=Ligue 1}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Caple |first=Alex |date= 12 August 2021|title=How good is Jeremy Doku and why do Liverpool want him? |url=https://www.rousingthekop.com/2021/08/12/how-good-is-jeremy-doku-and-why-do-liverpool-want-him/ |access-date=6 July 2023 |website=Rousing The Cop}}</ref> having scored 9 league goals in his first three seasons at Rennes. Due to his direct playing style and African heritage, Doku has often drawn comparisons with Senegalese forward [[Sadio Mané]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jeremy Doku's performance for Belgium at Euro 2020 has Liverpool supporters excited |url=https://footballghana.com/jeremy-dokus-performance-for-belgium-at-euro-2020-has-liverpool-supporters-excited |access-date=22 June 2021 |website=Football Ghana|date=22 June 2021 }}</ref> He is also frequently compared to Belgian compatriot [[Eden Hazard]] and is seen as his successor in the Belgium national team.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Schlupp |first=Jeffrey |date=3 September 2020 |title=Can Jérémy Doku become Eden Hazard's successor? |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/can-jeremy-doku-become-eden-hazards-successor |website=Ghana Soccernet}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Tully |first=David |date=15 October 2023 |title="That Is Very Intense" – City Star Makes Frank Admission After Being Asked Whether He Can Emulate Eden Hazard |url=https://mancitynews.com/blog/city-news-jeremy-doku-hazard-chelsea/ |website=Man City News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=19 February 2024 |title='He has everything'… Eden Hazard says Man City have a 21-year-old youngster who's heading right to the top |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/he-has-everything-eden-hazard-says-man-city-have-a-21-year-old-youngster-doku-whos-heading-right-to-the-top/ |website=manchestercity.news}}</ref> Doku considers Hazard to be his idol.<ref name="ligue1.com" /> He also cited [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Ronaldinho]] as influential in the early development of his footballing profile.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Burton |first=Chris |date=2 October 2023 |title=Revealed: How Lionel Messi & Ronaldinho inspired £56m Man City new boy Jeremy Doku and his dancing feet |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/revealed-how-lionel-messi-ronaldinho-inspired-56m-man-city-jeremy-doku/blt8152e41adac7521d#cs9396c9a4c9d30d87 |website=Goal (website)}}</ref>

===Reception===
The comparisons between Doku and Sadio Mané were sparked by German manager Jürgen Klopp, who allegedly made the comment to Doku's father as he was trying to recruit the youngster to Premier League side [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Williams |first=Joe |date=17 February 2020 |title=Parents claim Klopp called their son 'a potential successor to Mane' |url=https://www.football365.com/news/anderlecht-jeremy-doku-parents-claim-jurgen-klopp-liverpool-sadio-mane |website=Football365}}</ref> Upon calling up Doku for the Euro 2020, Belgium manager [[Roberto Martínez]] described him as "an exceptional talent who is very strong one on one".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jeremy Doku is an exceptional talent – Belgium coach Roberto Martinez |url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Jeremy-Doku-is-an-exceptional-talent-Belgium-coach-Roberto-Martinez-1043362 |access-date=26 August 2020 |website=GhanaWeb}}</ref> Martínez also praised Doku ahead of the World Cup in 2022, saying: "When I talk about him, I have to smile. He's one of those players who can bring magic to his game."<ref>{{Cite web |title=2022 World Cup: Belgium coach Roberto Martinez praises Jeremy Doku ahead of tournament |url=https://footballghana.com/2022-world-cup-belgium-coach-roberto-martinez-praises-jeremy-doku-ahead-of-tournament |access-date=12 November 2022 |website=Football Ghana|date=12 November 2022 }}</ref> In April 2023, former Arsenal captain [[Thierry Henry]] called Doku "extraordinary", adding that "he has never seen anyone so quick in his dribble".<ref>{{Cite web |title="Extraordinaire": Thierry Henry bluffé par les qualités techniques de Jérémy Doku |url=https://www.7sur7.be/diables-rouges/extraordinaire-thierry-henry-bluffe-par-les-qualites-techniques-de-jeremy-doku~a8e7006d/ |access-date=18 April 2023 |website=7sur7 (in French)}}</ref>

Former France international [[Samir Nasri]], who was briefly Doku's teammate at Anderlecht, described Doku as "an explosive dribbler" possessing "crazy quality" in one on one situations, predicting Doku will become one of the 20 best players in the world in the future.<ref name="ligue1.com"/> Former Anderlecht and Belgium forward [[Paul Van Himst]] echoed Nasri's words in October 2023 speaking for ''Voetbal Krant'', as he anticipated Doku will become one of the best players in the world within a year. Reflecting on the player who he had known as his grandson's teammate from the U16 and U18 levels at Anderlecht, Van Himst praised Doku, stating: "He is terribly fast, has so many qualities, what is good for him is that he is an individualist, but now that he left for Manchester City he will learn to play in a team".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sadhanand |first=Srinivas |date=1 October 2023 |title='One of the best players in the world': Pundit says Man City have a player who'll become a superstar in a year |url=https://www.manchestercity.news/one-of-the-best-players-in-the-world-pundit-paul-van-himst-says-man-city-have-a-player-doku-wholl-become-a-superstar-in-a-year/ |website=Manchester City News}}</ref>

Profiling the player for ''The Athletic'', Ahmed Walid said: "Whether it’s in tight spaces or in transition, Doku's ability to dribble past defenders makes them look as if they are defending at normal speed and that he is in fast forward".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Walid |first=Ahmed |title=Jeremy Doku: Rennes' electrifying two-footed dribbling machine |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4702691/2023/07/27/jeremy-doku-rennes-dribbling-machine/ |website=The Athletic|date=22 August 2023 }}</ref> Belgian football commentator Sacha Tavolieri has highlighted Doku's strength and his ability to "make incredible differences over two or three meters", while Frank Eeckhout, a journalist for the Belgian daily ''[[Het Laatste Nieuws]],'' evoking Doku's time at Anderlecht, said that "opposing players often had to commit faults to stop him and he caused quite a few yellow and red cards".<ref name="footballghana.com"/>

After two months of working with Doku since his transfer to Manchester City from Rennes, manager Pep Guardiola expressed surprise about the player's decision-making ability, saying "He reads every action and knows what to do, it's incredible how he can change the rhythm in five metres but when he is not able to do that he is able to take good decisions".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bray |first=Joe |date=4 November 2023 |title=Pep Guardiola admits Jeremy Doku has surprised Man City since £55m transfer |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/man-city-doku-bournemouth-transfer-28046690 |website=Manchester Evening News}}</ref> Guardiola said that when Doku has the ball he always creates something for the crowd, and "everyone gets excited – myself too!". In the post-match interview after Doku recorded four assists against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] on 4 November 2023, the former [[FC Barcelona]] coach stated that "normally there are a lot of wingers that go inside, but this guy, you don't know what he's going to do".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clayton |first=David |date=4 November 2023 |title=Guardiola thrilled by Doku performance |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-6-1-bournemouth-pep-guardiola-reaction-63834715 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref>

[[Kevin De Bruyne]] called Doku "a diamond in the rough" after the forward's debut for the Belgium national team in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |title=He's a rough diamond – De Bruyne showers praise on Jeremy Doku |url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/He-s-a-rough-diamond-De-Bruyne-showers-praise-on-Jeremy-Doku-1056235 |access-date=14 August 2023 |website=Football Ghana}}</ref> In an interview for Belgian media outlet ''Eleven'' in 2023, Rennes and Belgium defender [[Arthur Theate]] stated that "it is impossible to defend against Jérémy Doku".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arthur Theate: "You can't defend against Jérémy Doku" |url=https://euro.dayfr.com/sports/415908.html |access-date=7 July 2023 |website=DayFR Euro}}</ref> In 2021, PSG star [[Kylian Mbappé]] said: "Recently, I was speaking with my father about a player who impressed me because of his speed, and that is Doku at Rennes", adding that "in five years as a professional, I have never seen someone demonstrate so much power from a standing start."<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Calaghan |first=Rory |date=27 June 2023 |title="So much power..." – Kylian Mbappe blown away by Liverpool transfer target Jeremy Doku |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/liverpool-transfer-news-mbappe-doku-rennes-424634-20230627 |website=SPORTbible}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Doku was born in [[Antwerp]], Belgium, and is of Ghanaian descent.<ref>{{cite web |title=Video: English giants Liverpool set to sign Ghanaian youngster Jeremy Doku |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/english-giants-liverpool-set-to-sign-ghanaian-youngster-jeremy-doku |website=GhanaSoccernet|date=7 May 2018 }}</ref> He is the second child of David and Belinda and has one older brother and two younger sisters. His father is a former athlete, while his brother Jefferson was a part of Anderlecht's youth academy.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hendrix |first=Hale |title=Jeremy Doku Childhood Story Plus Untold Biography Facts |url=https://lifebogger.com/jeremy-doku-childhood-biography-story-facts/ |website=Life Bogger |access-date=7 July 2023 |archive-date=8 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230708090027/https://lifebogger.com/jeremy-doku-childhood-biography-story-facts/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> Despite Doku's passion for football from a young age, his parents were focused on giving their youngest son an education, and he attended primary school in Antwerp and then a boarding school in Brussels while training between classes.<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 August 2021 |title=Top Facts about Jeremy Doku, The Thriving Loner |url=https://sportmob.com/en/article/969325-top-facts-about-jeremy-doku-the-thriving-loner |website=SportMob}}</ref>

In August 2025, Doku got engaged to Shireen Erin Lyannda Raymond in Dubai and it was reported through his YouTube documentary.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jeremy Doku proposes to his girlfriend in Dubai after Ghana visit [Video] {{!}} Pulse Ghana |url=https://www.pulse.com.gh/articles/sports/jeremy-doku-proposes-to-his-girlfriend-in-dubai-after-ghana-visit-video-2025080814331507167 |access-date=19 August 2025 |website=www.pulse.com.gh |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CsWqRpbuk8 |title=Jeremy Doku {{!}} Episode 2 {{!}} When Two Become One |date=6 August 2025 |last=Jeremy Doku Official |access-date=19 August 2025 |via=YouTube}}</ref> They got married in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 October 2025 |title=Elle a dit "oui" : Jérémy Doku franchit une étape importante dans sa vie personnelle |url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2025-10-15/elle-a-dit-oui--jeremy-doku-franchit-une-etape-importante-dans-sa-vie-personnelle |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=Walfoot.be |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sports |first=R. T. L. |date=15 October 2025 |title=Jérémy Doku n'a pas décollé avec la Belgique lundi soir : le Diable Rouge s'est marié |url=http://www.rtl.be/sport/football/diables-rouges/jeremy-doku-na-pas-decolle-avec-la-belgique-lundi-soir-le-diable-rouge-sest/2025-10-15/article/767019 |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=RTL Info |language=fr}}</ref>

Doku is a [[Christianity|Christian]]. He was baptized in September 2025.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stone |first1=Simon |title=Doku speaks about religious end to 'victory day' |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c2knvkw4qkwo |website=BBC |access-date=17 November 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Doering |first1=Joshua |title=Manchester City's Jeremy Doku credits electric start to having 'God in my life' |url=https://sportsspectrum.com/sport/soccer/2025/11/11/manchester-city-jeremy-doku-god-in-my-life/ |website=Sports Spectrum |access-date=17 November 2025}}</ref>

